Engineering Services

Skyward’s engineering services include research & development, modeling & simulation, design of experiments (DOE) analysis, and systems engineering. Skyward’s defense experience includes weapon system analysis, system sustainment, survivability / vulnerability / lethality analysis, combat data analysis, vulnerability reduction, and much more.

Read More

Test & Evaluation

Skyward is a leader in test and evaluation, with significant experience in combat survivability and is a recognized expert in Live Fire Test & Evaluation. Services include strategy development, liaison support, test planning, onsite test monitoring and data collection, data synthesis and analysis, and test reporting.

Read More

3D Services

Skyward performs 3D scanning and metrology services, scanning everything from small parts to full aircraft, develops parametric 3D models, performs full dimensional parts inspection, and performs reverse engineering. Skyward partners with 3D printing/additive manufacturing companies to offer a full range of emerging technologies.

Read More

Vehicle Systems

Skyward supports vehicle systems integration and performs technology development, including Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR) projects to advance the state-of-the-art. Skyward has developed an internal team of experts and numerous partnerships to pursue the use of Unmanned Aerial System (UAS)/drone technology for unique and commercially-viable business applications.

Read More

 

Who We Are

Skyward Ltd. is a small business headquartered adjacent to Wright-Patterson Air Force Base in Dayton, Ohio. Incorporated in Ohio as an LLC in 1997, Skyward meets client needs by leveraging its talents, experience, small business advantages, its willingness to partner with other organizations, and its capability to apply knowledge where no other experts exist.

Skyward provides the highest quality professional engineering services and custom solutions to our Government and Industry partners. We focus in the areas of engineering services, test & evaluation, 3D metrology and scanning, and unmanned systems.
